---

Peel and slice the @red onion{1} in half lengthways through the root. Slice the onion into ultra-thin 'half moons' and keep 1 tbsp to the side. Add the rest to a large #non-stick pan{} with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and cover with a #lid{}. Cook on low heat until step 6.

Pre-heat the #oven{} to 200 degrees and very finely dice the tbsp of remaining onion. Add this to the @minced beef{450%g} in a #bowl{} with the @mustard{1%tbsp}, @dried oregano{1%tsp}, @cumin{1%tsp} and @flat leaf parsley{1%tbsp}(finely chopped). Add @salt{1/2%tsp} and very thoroughly mix the ingredients, then form into golf balls. Stick your thumb into each, then fill with a bit of grated @mature cheddar cheese{4%tbsp}(grated) before closing them up tight!

> We recommend enlisting the help of your junior sous chefs squeezing them (the meatballs!) quite tightly so they hold together.

Place the meatballs on a #baking tray{} and cook on the top shelf of the oven for ~{20%minutes}.

> They should be nicely browned off when you remove them from the oven.

Boil a #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the potatoes. Peel and chop the @potatoes{4} into roughly 3cm cubes. Boil them in the water for around ~{10%minutes} or until you can easily slip a knife through them. Drain and mash with a bit of @milk{as needed} and @?butter{as needed} and a good pinch of @salt{}.

Meanwhile, peel and dice the @carrot{1}(peeled and diced into tiny cubes) into tiny cubes (1/2 cm if your knife skills allow). Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1}(core removed and sliced into matchsticks) and slice into thin matchsticks.

Take the lid off the onions (which should be nice and soft) and add the carrot and pepper. Add the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}. Give it a stir and turn the heat to medium. Cook for around ~{8%minutes}.

Once all the veggies are soft, add in the @tomato passata{2%tbsp} and the @muscovado sugar{1%tsp}. Add @salt{1/4%tsp} and a few grinds of @pepper{a few grinds} (then taste and add more if needed). Bubble away for ~{5%minutes} on medium-low heat before adding in the meatballs. Cook for a further ~{5%minutes} before gently stirring in @flat leaf parsley{1%tbsp}(finely chopped).

Serve with your mash and another sprinkle of parsley.